 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.14","title":"[audit][service] Respect DNS poll interval after resolution failures","description":"DnsServiceDiscovery::poll_discover() increments error_count on resolve failure but leaves last_resolve unchanged. When a hostname is failing, repeated poll_discover() calls therefore retry DNS immediately on every poll instead of honoring poll_interval, which can create hot-loop retry pressure in callers that poll frequently. Fix by recording the failure attempt time, preserving deterministic diff behavior for successful resolutions, and adding a regression test that proves repeated failures within the interval do not increment error_count again until the interval elapses or invalidate() is called.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"ScarletRaven","estimated_minutes":60,"created_at":"2026-03-08T18:41:46.886779808Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-08T19:36:05.520817992Z","closed_at":"2026-03-08T19:36:05.520798145Z","close_reason":"Already implemented in-tree and released by assignee: src/service/discover.rs now records last_resolve on DNS resolution failure, and the file includes regressions dns_discovery_failed_resolution_respects_poll_interval plus dns_discovery_invalidate_forces_retry_after_failed_resolution. ScarletRaven reported rch-backed cargo check -p asupersync --lib and cargo clippy -p asupersync --lib -- -D warnings passing on this slice; narrowed test-target runs remained stuck in the known rch queue/post-run transport path, with no concrete failing output surfaced.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","service"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.14","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-08T18:41:46.886779808Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.15","title":"[audit][browser-reactor] Stop wake() from fabricating readiness without host signals","description":"BrowserReactor::wake() currently snapshots every registered token's interest mask into the pending event queue. That violates the Reactor::wake() contract in src/runtime/reactor/mod.rs, which says wake() should only break poll() out early and must not invent I/O readiness. In the browser scaffold this means a plain wake can report false READABLE/WRITABLE readiness for unrelated tokens before any host callback calls notify_ready(). Fix wake() so host readiness flows only through notify_ready(), keep coalescing semantics sane, and add deterministic regressions proving wake() with registered tokens yields no synthetic readiness while notify_ready() still works.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"SilentSpring","created_at":"2026-03-08T22:24:27.806591954Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-08T22:31:50.427623508Z","closed_at":"2026-03-08T22:31:50.427598282Z","close_reason":"Completed: BrowserReactor wake no longer fabricates readiness; targeted browser-reactor tests pass via rch; cargo check --all-targets passes via rch; workspace clippy still fails in unrelated transport/blocking_pool files.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","reactor","wasm"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.15","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-08T22:24:27.806591954Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.16","title":"[audit][service] Make DNS discovery ordering deterministic","description":"Patch src/service/discover.rs so DnsServiceDiscovery does not leak HashSet iteration order through poll_discover() change batches or endpoints(). Add focused regression tests for deterministic endpoint snapshots and deterministic change ordering.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"TopazLake","created_at":"2026-03-08T22:25:25.418115510Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-08T22:57:38.267301557Z","closed_at":"2026-03-08T22:57:38.267277983Z","close_reason":"Duplicate of completed bead asupersync-1qfd0.17 created during hanging br create attempts","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","determinism","service"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.16","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-08T22:25:25.418115510Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
